Property Accountant
Confidential Company - ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 10:38:19
Ref. JB3047831
Job Description
- Maintaining financial records for capitalized equipment, vehicles and real estate
- Overseeing changes in asset management such as disposal or location, and the addition of new purchases
- Conducts periodic reviews, audits and inventory as necessary along with providing guidance to department managers for maintenance and repair of the company's equipment or other assets
- Updating tenant records to reflect changes in tenants, rent, utilities, repair and maintenance, and common area charges, along with invoice preparation for tenants
- Generate reports on new asset purchases, capitalization, management and disposal of a company's assets
- Manage collections for tenant invoices, generate reports reflecting payments or collection activities and ensure that all tenant financial records are current.
Skills
- 1 to 3 years experience in real estate industry
- Advanced computer and spreadsheet skills
- Knowledge of federal and state real estate laws, and may require specific experience with a property or asset management software
- Ability to set up escrow accounts and portfolios
- Create and manage budgets and maintain financial records and transactions with respect to assets
- Have excellent verbal and written communication skills
Education
Banking, Finance, Business
